{"title_page": "Broadway\u2013Chambers Building", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=August 2019}}\n{{Short description|Office skyscraper in Manhattan, New York}}\n{{Infobox building\n| name                = Broadway\u2013Chambers Building\n| image               = Broadway-Chambers Building.jpg\n| image_alt           =\n| image_size          = 225px\n| caption             = (2012)\n| map_type            = New York City\n| map_alt             = \n| map_caption         = Location in New York City\n| architectural_style = [[Beaux-Arts architecture|Beaux-Arts]]\n| location            = 277 Broadway<br>[[Manhattan]], [[New York City]]\n| address             = \n| location_town       = \n| location_country    = \n| coordinates         = {{coord|40|42|52|N|74|00|23|W|region:US-NY|format=dms|display=inline,title}}\n| groundbreaking_date = \n| start_date          = 1899\n| completion_date     = 1900\n| height              = \n| roof                = {{convert|225|ft|m}}\n| top_floor           = \n| other_dimensions    = \n| floor_count         = 18\n| floor_area          = \n| main_contractor     = [[George A. Fuller Company]]\n| architect           = [[Cass Gilbert]]\n| architecture_firm   = \n| structural_engineer = Purdy & Henderson\n| services_engineer   = \n| civil_engineer      = \n| other_designers     = \n| quantity_surveyor   = \n| awards              = \n| designations        = \n| ren_architect       = \n| ren_firm            = \n| ren_str_engineer    = \n| ren_serv_engineer   = \n| ren_civ_engineer    = \n| ren_oth_designers   = \n| ren_qty_surveyor    = \n| ren_awards          =\n| parking             =\n| url                 = \n| embedded            = \n{{Designation list\n| embed               = yes\n| designation1        = NYCL\n| designation1_date   = January 14, 1992\n| designation1_number = 1753\n}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Broadway\u2013Chambers Building''', located at 277 [[Broadway (Manhattan)|Broadway]] on the northwest corner of [[Chambers Street (Manhattan)|Chambers Street]] in the [[Civic Center, Manhattan|Civic Center]] / [[TriBeCa]] neighborhood of [[Manhattan]], [[New York City]], was constructed from 1899 to 1900, and was architect [[Cass Gilbert]]'s first design in the city.  The 18-story office building is designed in the [[Beaux-Arts architecture|Beaux-Arts style]].<ref name=desrep /><ref name=nycland>{{cite nycland|page=30}}</ref>\n\nOn the building's completion in 1900, the critic [[Montgomery Schuyler]] said that it was \"...the summation of that type of design of a tall building,\"<ref name=desrep>Urbaneilli, Elisa (ed.) [http://s-media.nyc.gov/agencies/lpc/lp/1753.pdf \"Broadway\u2013Chambers Building Dasignation Report\"] [[New York Landmarks Preservation Commission]] (January 14, 1992)</ref> and in 1998 [[Herbert Muschamp]] wrote in ''[[The New York Times]]'' of Gilbert's design:\n\n<blockquote>[He] refined the proportions between [the building's] elements and articulated them by using different materials for each: stone base, brick shaft, [[terra cotta]] crown. The brickwork, red flecked with blue, is especially fine. In contrast with the light-colored stone and terra cotta, it gives an almost colonial feel to an otherwise classically conceived structure. Garlands, cornucopias and a polychrome penthouse arcade garnish the composition.<ref name=nyt98>Muschamp, Herbert [https://www.nytimes.com/1998/10/09/arts/critic-s-notebook-cass-gilbert-and-the-city-eclectic.html \"Cass Gilbert And the City Eclectic \"] ''[[New York Times]]'' (October 9, 1998)</ref></blockquote>\n\nThe building incorporates one of Gilbert's trademarks, the extensive use of architectural sculpture on the [[cornice]] of the arcade at the top of the building, which includes the heads of lions and women.<ref>{{cite AIA4|pages=77\u201378}}</ref> Gilbert went on to be one of the pre-eminent architects of his time, designing the [[Woolworth Building]] and the [[United States Supreme Court building]], among many others.<ref name=\"cassgilbertsociety1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.cassgilbertsociety.org/architect/buildings/nyc-broadway-chambers.html |title=Cass Gilbert \u2013 the Architect \u2013 Buildings \u2013 Broadway Chambers Building, New York City |publisher=Cass Gilbert Society |date= |accessdate=2010-02-09}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last=Fenske|first=Gail |title=The skyscraper and the city: the Woolworth Building and the making of modern New York  |publisher=University of Chicago Press|location=Chicago|year=2008|page=[https://archive.org/details/skyscrapercitywo0000fens/page/105 105]|isbn=978-0-226-24141-8 |url=https://archive.org/details/skyscrapercitywo0000fens|url-access=registration|quote=Broadway Chambers building.}}</ref>\n\nSeveral companies collaborated to create an exhibit about the construction of the building at the [[Paris Exposition of 1900]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1900/06/17/archives/civil-engineering-and-trans-portation.html |author=Baker, A. C. |title=Civil Engineering and Transportation |newspaper=[[The New York Times]] |date=June 17, 1900 |page=19 |quote=This is a collective exhibit, participated in by twenty-six firms, and illustrates the construction of the Broadway Chambers Building. New York. |accessdate=2010-02-09}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last=George A. Fuller Company|title=Broadway Chambers; a modern office building, exhibited by models at the Paris exposition, 1900.|publisher=G. A. Fuller co.|location=New York|year=1900|pages=61|lccn=00005410}}</ref>\n\nThe Broadway\u2013Chambers Building was designated a [[List of New York City Landmarks|New York City landmark]] in 1992.<ref name=desrep />\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of New York City Designated Landmarks in Manhattan below 14th Street]]\n\n==References==\n'''Notes'''\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{commonscat-inline|Broadway-Chambers Building}}\n*{{skyscraperpage|5345}}\n*[http://www.emporis.com/building/broadwaychambersbuilding-newyorkcity-ny-usa Broadway\u2013Chambers Building] on ''[[Emporis.com]]''\n